  "prompt": "Which is the best camera phone performance under 10000?",
  "response": "When looking for the best camera phone under \u20b910,000 in India, several models stand out due to their camera performance and overall value. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n### 1. **Realme Narzo 50i Prime**\n   - **Camera**: 8MP primary sensor\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b97,000 - \u20b98,000\n   - **Pros**: Good for the price, decent daylight photography, and reliable performance for budget users.\n\n### 2. **Samsung Galaxy F04**\n   - **Camera**: 13MP primary sensor\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b98,000 - \u20b99,000\n   - **Pros**: Offers better resolution than many competitors in this range, decent camera performance in good lighting conditions.\n\n### 3. **Redmi 10A Sport**\n   - **Camera**: 13MP primary sensor\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b99,000 - \u20b910,000\n   - **Pros**: Good camera quality for the price, decent low-light performance compared to others in this segment.\n\n### 4. **itel S23**\n   - **Camera**: 50MP primary sensor\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b98,000 - \u20b99,000\n   - **Pros**: High-resolution camera sensor offers good detail in well-lit conditions, competitive for the budget segment.\n\n### Camera Performance Comparison:\n- **Daylight Photography**: The itel S23 and Redmi 10A Sport tend to perform better due to their higher resolution sensors.\n- **Low-Light Photography**: The Redmi 10A Sport and Samsung Galaxy F04 might offer slightly better performance, though results are generally modest in this price range.\n- **Overall Value**: The itel S23 stands out for offering a 50MP camera at a budget price, making it a strong contender if camera quality is your primary concern.\n\n### Final Recommendation:\nIf camera performance is your top priority, the **itel S23** with its 50MP camera provides the best value under \u20b910,000. However, consider your overall needs, as other factors like battery life, software, and build quality can also influence your decision.\n\nAlways check the latest reviews and possibly visit a store to see the camera performance in person, as real-world usage can differ from specifications on paper.",
